gujarati.context:
Ati chmatkari che eh, thaya sukhi seve jan jeh;
Tapphal mahe tiyan tart, jiyan tap karyu aage bharat.

English translation:

This is very difficult to bear, it makes people happy; 
The fruit of penance will be obtained there, but here one must do penance first.

Here is the translation:

Done action there worship Pujan, done Muktanath's sight;
Afterward bears done Tap Jivan, one sits down even there.

Here is the translation:

"I have taken the attention of God Rama's sun, performed daily ablution in Gandaki; 
My mind serves the Lord without bondage, whatever fruit or flower comes is given."

This is what it means:

Someone else's suffering is seen as suffering, my mind is troubled by the Lord's sorrow; 
The path of devotion has taken hold of my divine body, It remains with me at your feet, doing what you want to be done.

Ati krisi uvha ek paghe, nahi dekhii saktaan te drage; 
Jaanyu laddhadi padeshay naath, khama khama kahii dey hath.

(Extreme difficulty is on one leg, cannot be seen that much; 
The known misfortune will fall upon him, loudly loudly he will say with his hand.)

Here is the translation:

My fate is in my hands, my worries on my shoulders;
Conch shells are tied with karma, I have put up a boundary around me.
